{"comments":"Device-dependent units - measurements that depend on display hardware.\n\nA pixel has no inherent physical size. A \"1920px\" image could be:\n- 20 inches wide on a 96 PPI monitor\n- 13 inches wide on a 144 PPI laptop\n- 200 inches wide on a projector\n\n## Unit Distinctions\n\n- **DevicePixel**: Actual hardware pixels on the display\n- **CSSPixel**: Reference pixel at 96 PPI (CSS spec)\n- **Pixel**: Generic discrete pixel (context determines meaning)\n\n## Conversion Requires Context\n\nTo convert between device units and physical units, you need:\n- PPI (pixels per inch) of the display\n- Device pixel ratio (for HiDPI/Retina displays)\n\nSee `Dimension.Context` for conversion functions.\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[94,29],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Dimension/Device.purs","start":[94,15]},"title":"Pixel"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Dimension","Device"],"Pixel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[96,36],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Dimension/Device.purs","start":[96,1]},"title":"eqPixel"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Dimension","Device"],"Pixel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[97,38],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Dimension/Device.purs","start":[97,1]},"title":"ordPixel"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"content